Russian Equity Movers: Gazprom, Norilsk, Rosneft Are Active

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-08-09T10:04:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-09/russian-equity-movers-gazprom-norilsk-rosneft-are-active.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  retreated
5.5 percent to 1,431.41 by 1:47 p.m.in Moscow, paring an earlier
slide of as much as 7.5 percent. The dollar-denominated RTS
Index sank 7.9 percent to 1,526.5.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Gazprom (GAZP RX), the natural gas export monopoly,
sank the most in almost three years as oil fell. The shares lost
as much as 9.5 percent, the most since November 2008, and last
traded 5.8 percent lower at 160.37 rubles.  OAO GMK Norilsk Nickel (GMKN),  Russia ’s biggest mining
company, headed for its lowest level since December, slipping
5.3 percent to 6,340 rubles as copper declined.  OAO Rosneft (ROSN RX), the country’s largest oil producer,
slid 4.6 percent to 197.75 rubles as crude slumped in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
